    • Method Detail

      • hasStoredSdkSettings

        public boolean hasStoredSdkSettings()
        This method can check to see if there are any stored SdkSettings in the SharedPreferences
        Returns:
        true if the SharedPreferences contains the SDK_SETTINGS_KEY, false otherwise.

      • getStoredSdkSettings

        @Deprecated
public SdkSettings getStoredSdkSettings()
        Deprecated. 
        Gets the stored SdkSettings from the SharedPreferences.

        If the SdkSettings were found but do not deserialise correctly then the saved settings will be removed using deleteStoredSdkSettings() as this is probably due to irrecoverable differences in the stored model and a new one.

        Deprecated. Use getStoredSettings()

        Returns:
        The SdkSettings if they are available in storage or null if there were no saved settings or there was a problem with deserialisation.

      • getStoredSettings

        public MobileSettings getStoredSettings()
        Gets the stored MobileSettings from the SharedPreferences.

        If the MobileSettings were found but do not deserialise correctly then the saved settings will be removed using deleteStoredSettings() as this is probably due to irrecoverable differences in the stored model and a new one.

        Returns:
        The MobileSettings if they are available in storage or null if there were no saved settings or there was a problem with deserialisation.

      • setStoredSdkSettings

        @Deprecated
public void setStoredSdkSettings(SdkSettings sdkSettings)
        Deprecated. 
        Saves the supplied SdkSettings to SharedPreferences.

        If the supplied SdkSettings is null then this will not save the settings to SharedPreferences. If the intention is to delete them then please use deleteStoredSdkSettings()

        Parameters:
        sdkSettings - The SdkSettings to save.

      • deleteStoredSdkSettings

        @Deprecated
public void deleteStoredSdkSettings()
        Deprecated. 
        Deletes any stored SdkSettings that may be present in the SharedPreferences.

        Note that this clears all keys that have been created by this class. Please be wary of this if you are using this class to store more than just the JSON representation of the SdkSettings using the SDK_SETTINGS_KEY

      • setStoredSettings

        public void setStoredSettings(MobileSettings mobileSettings)
        Saves the supplied MobileSettings to SharedPreferences.

        If the supplied MobileSettings is null then this will not save the settings to SharedPreferences. If the intention is to delete them then please use deleteStoredSettings()

        Parameters:
        mobileSettings - The MobileSettings to save.

      • deleteStoredSettings

        public void deleteStoredSettings()
        Deletes any stored MobileSettings that may be present in the SharedPreferences.

        Note that this clears all keys that have been created by this class. Please be wary of this if you are using this class to store more than just the JSON representation of the MobileSettings using the MOBILE_SETTINGS_KEY
